<ul><li>For a point source that emit&nbsp;\(n\)&nbsp;gamma photons per second, each of energy&nbsp;\(hf\), the&nbsp;<b>radiation energy per second</b>&nbsp;from the source&nbsp;\(=nhf\)</li><li>At distance&nbsp;\(r\)&nbsp;from the source, all the photons emitted from the source pass through a total area of&nbsp;\(4\pi r^2\).\[I=\frac{nhf}{4\pi r^2}\]</li></ul>